SUITE.NAME: All in Web Application Coverage Results

task.summary:
ORF display fixed, and fixed tests from the ORF Swap.
Additionally, changed it so that the 'last character index' for the ORF Location is the character after the ORF. This corrects the length to be the actual expected length. Will see if this produces the proper expected results or needs more fixing! Tests say it's fine, but I have some doubts.

Misc display quality changes
Changed the presentation of the list a little bit again, and highlighting of the selected ORF on the contig inspection page. Just QoL things and preparing for the next step of displaying the full list of ORF Locations.

ORF Info display and more presentation improvements
More improvements on presentation (footer, moved around some items for ORF chart). Mainly though, when a user clicks an ORF Location now, they can see information about it below the ORF Location chart, including frame number, length, start, end and characters.

ORF Location index labels and loading button on Inspect
Clicking Inspect after the parameter settings will now change the value of the button to say 'Loading...', just to give the user some feedback that they have actually clicked the button. A dedicated loading page would be better, but is out of scope for this project. Also, I've added labels for the current index for the first character of each line in the display of the ORF Location characters. Just makes it look a little nicer. Along with this, I cleaned up the colouring of the first and last character as there were a few instances where the colouring would be misplace/missed entirely, caused by the ordering of the conditional statements in the code.

Moved some items around in code
Changed the colour of the start codon and moved some Javascript into utilities file.

Result tabs, ORF list, improved viewing
Made things nicer to look at (not perfect, header/footer need work), mainly with the ORF page, I've made the ORF bars a little smaller so they fit better on the page. May have to increase them again a bit in order to deal with smaller ORF Locations. Also added the list of ORF Locations down the right side of the ORF chart, with a button to view the ORF. I haven't hooked this into actually displaying the information about the ORF yet though. That comes next Also added tabs to the results quality page thing. Looks nicer than the endless scrolling. Credit to the list goes to http://red-team-design.com/css3-jquery-folder-tabs/

Credit to the list goes to http://red-team-design.com/css3-jquery-folder-tabs/

Improved Codon highlighting
All start and stop codons are now highlighted. Fully changed the way in which the ORF Location characters are built to be displayed to accommodate for this. Much better!

Further improved display
Gave a scroll box to the list of ORF Locations for when there are a lot of them. Added the number of contigs in the shown list and number of discarded contigs to the contig list after input. Involved adding a new class ContigResult in order to hold the previously kept list of contigs for use in the inspection and the new discarded variable. Small misc css changes here and there.

Recompiled and rerun tests for CI
CI was complaining as the changes to the last build changed tests and I hadn't rerun them yet (expected CI to do it for me, little did I know it would of course pick up the class files to use, which didn't exist)

It wasn't the tests, it was the missing file
So, apparently the new class just didn't get added to version control. Since I changed the way I check in classes, I guess it doesn't automatically add new classes to VCS? Ah well, done now.

More view changes, sorting the list of ORF Locs by length
As title, changed the scroll box for ORF Locations again just because I didn't like how the headers were lined up. Also sorted the list of ORF Locations by longest to shorest in the model, and this comes through to the view to be seen. The clicking of the ORFs still works, as even in a different order the ids/indexes of the ORF Locations in the list are the same (as that's how they're put down.

It wasn't the tests, it was the missing file
So, apparently the new class just didn't get added to version control. Since I changed the way I check in classes, I guess it doesn't automatically add new classes to VCS? Ah well, done now.

Keeping track of the number of N characters in a contig
Now displaying the number of N characters in a contig on the contig list, and what percentage of the total size of the contig length that is. May help the user themselves decide if it's worth assessing that particular contig or not.
